<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1373</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-03T18:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7128. There is reason to believe that British cable censor has
                                recently suppressed messages in code passing between the Russian
                                Ambassador here and the Russian Ambassador in Paris.</p>
                            <p>Please ascertain and report for our confidential information attitude
                                of British Government towards these Russian officials. The
                                Department has confidence in Russian Ambassador here and grants him
                                unrestricted cable privileges.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>